00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:49,980
   
   

17
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,160
Cong! Xi Chi!

18
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:55,320
- Aunt Chen. 
 - Are you waiting for Huan Er?

19
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,420
- Were you doing grocery shopping? 
 - Yes.

20
00:01:57,420 --> 00:01:59,080
What are you cooking for lunch?

21
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:01,780
Stir-fried tomato and scrambled eggs.

22
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:03,370
Chen Huan Er!

23
00:02:03,370 --> 00:02:05,810
Look at the time. What took you so long today?

24
00:02:05,810 --> 00:02:09,327
I pulled an all-nighter reading.

25
00:02:09,327 --> 00:02:11,927
Are you that diligent?

26
00:02:11,927 --> 00:02:14,167
   

27
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:17,557
Neuropsychology?

28
00:02:17,557 --> 00:02:19,007
I think you're pretty neurotic.

29
00:02:19,007 --> 00:02:22,237
You don't know. This book is earth-shattering.

30
00:02:22,237 --> 00:02:25,237
Whoever gets it is so lucky.

31
00:02:25,237 --> 00:02:29,507
- What do you mean? 
 - Do you know what the Einstellung effect is?

32
00:02:30,207 --> 00:02:33,287
What nonsense are you talking about? That sounds like a swear word.

33
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:35,047
The Einstellung effect.

34
00:02:35,047 --> 00:02:40,487
It's a mechanized state of mind that will affect how you act later.

35
00:02:40,487 --> 00:02:41,797
Amazing.

36
00:02:41,797 --> 00:02:42,837
You even know that.

37
00:02:42,837 --> 00:02:45,487
As expected from the top student.

38
00:02:45,487 --> 00:02:48,227
So what does it mean?

39
00:02:48,957 --> 00:02:50,677
Let me show you.

40
00:02:50,677 --> 00:02:53,507
Fine. But do you know how to do that?

41
00:03:00,487 --> 00:03:03,047
- What are you doing? 
 - Don't move.

42
00:03:03,047 --> 00:03:06,597
That's painful, Chen Huan Er! What are you doing?

43
00:03:08,767 --> 00:03:10,927
What are you doing, Chen Huan Er?

44
00:03:10,927 --> 00:03:12,637
This is the Einstellung effect.

45
00:03:12,637 --> 00:03:16,197
In layman's terms, it's called predisposition.

46
00:03:16,907 --> 00:03:19,107
You could've just told me. Why did you attack me?

47
00:03:19,107 --> 00:03:21,607
I was afraid you wouldn't understand.

48
00:03:21,607 --> 00:03:24,077
Young man, you should study more.

49
00:03:24,077 --> 00:03:25,667
Let's go.

50
00:03:26,637 --> 00:03:29,007
Cong, what book did you choose?

51
00:03:29,007 --> 00:03:31,117
The Catcher in the Rye.

52
00:03:31,117 --> 00:03:33,287
What kind of book is that?

53
00:03:33,287 --> 00:03:35,487
No, Chen Huan Er.

54
00:03:35,487 --> 00:03:38,807
You just wanted to attack me, right?

55
00:03:45,357 --> 00:03:48,947
Lin Shuang, this is for you. I hope you like it.

56
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:58,757
What can you achieve with romance?

57
00:04:08,767 --> 00:04:10,237
Don't just spray it.

58
00:04:10,237 --> 00:04:13,927
First, you need to find out what scent the person you want to give the book to likes.

59
00:04:13,927 --> 00:04:16,157
You have to get it right.

60
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:26,727
You should cut it out.

61
00:04:26,727 --> 00:04:29,757
You're making the air all musty with this nonsense. I can already feel my allergies acting up.

62
00:04:29,757 --> 00:04:31,237
I made this scent myself.

63
00:04:31,237 --> 00:04:32,647
I just sprayed it.

64
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:34,797
The after-note smells amazing.

65
00:04:34,797 --> 00:04:36,197
You have no taste at all.

66
00:04:36,197 --> 00:04:37,847
I don't want to have the same taste as you.

67
00:04:37,847 --> 00:04:39,087
You are so annoying!

68
00:04:39,087 --> 00:04:41,237
Why are you so different from Song Cong?

69
00:04:41,237 --> 00:04:43,557
Song Cong, do you want to decorate your book?

70
00:04:43,557 --> 00:04:45,997
I'm just going to hand it in as it is.

71
00:04:47,317 --> 00:04:49,317
Jing Xi Chi, do you have any newspapers?

72
00:04:49,317 --> 00:04:51,727
I want to decorate my book too.

73
00:04:51,727 --> 00:04:54,137
Thank you.

74
00:04:54,137 --> 00:04:56,997
Does anyone need a book wrapper?

75
00:04:56,997 --> 00:04:58,287
Give me one.

76
00:04:58,287 --> 00:05:00,437
- Thank you. 
 - You are welcome.

77
00:05:09,117 --> 00:05:12,647
 This book makes me understand my mind even better. 

78
00:05:12,647 --> 00:05:14,757
 It sounds weird, right? 

79
00:05:14,757 --> 00:05:16,487
 You'll understand after reading it. 

80
00:05:16,487 --> 00:05:21,197
 I hope you have as much fun reading it as I did. 

81
00:06:50,997 --> 00:06:53,197
Qi Qi.

82
00:06:53,197 --> 00:06:54,997
What are you looking for?

83
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,967
Is there a book you want to find?

84
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:59,147
Let me help you with that.

85
00:07:01,287 --> 00:07:04,287
It's okay. I just don't know which book to choose.

86
00:07:04,287 --> 00:07:06,877
Have you made up your mind?

87
00:07:06,877 --> 00:07:08,437
Not yet.

88
00:07:08,437 --> 00:07:10,757
I still want to look around.

89
00:07:12,797 --> 00:07:16,197
Are you sure Song Cong chose The Catcher in the Rye?

90
00:07:16,197 --> 00:07:17,560
You've already asked me so many times.

91
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,847
I'm sure. He told me himself.

92
00:07:19,847 --> 00:07:21,437
So, I'm sure.

93
00:07:21,437 --> 00:07:25,277
By the way, why do you care so much about him?

94
00:07:26,997 --> 00:07:28,640
I'm not.

95
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:31,797
Our class is about to start soon. Let's go.

96
00:07:31,797 --> 00:07:33,487
I'll choose this one. This book is huge.

97
00:07:33,487 --> 00:07:34,527
Huan Er, let's go.

98
00:07:34,527 --> 00:07:36,147
I'm coming.

99
00:07:38,117 --> 00:07:40,027
I'm sorry.

100
00:07:41,637 --> 00:07:49,467
   

101
00:07:57,277 --> 00:08:01,357
   

102
00:08:01,357 --> 00:08:02,757
Are you kidding me?

103
00:08:02,757 --> 00:08:05,572
Who chose these College Entrance Examination Mock Tests?

104
00:08:05,572 --> 00:08:08,040
We study three years of senior high for the college entrance exam.

105
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:10,437
May you score well after getting this book.

106
00:08:10,437 --> 00:08:15,317
Li Tian. Are you crazy? You're too obsessed with studying.

107
00:08:17,607 --> 00:08:19,927
I won't read this book. I'll return it later.

108
00:08:19,927 --> 00:08:21,997
I'll let others suffer through it.

109
00:08:28,877 --> 00:08:31,167
The Catcher in the Rye?

110
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:32,647
You have quite good taste.

111
00:08:32,647 --> 00:08:37,447
But unfortunately, Salinger is not one of the leading English literature authors.

112
00:08:37,447 --> 00:08:40,347
Mind your own business. I like it.

113
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:23,147
    
  (T/N: Counting in fives using the character 正.) 

114
00:09:43,087 --> 00:09:45,807
   

115
00:09:55,147 --> 00:09:59,477
 She took the long way around just to talk to him. 

116
00:09:59,477 --> 00:10:03,957
 It was just a simple question, but she made him spend so much time teaching her. 

117
00:10:03,957 --> 00:10:08,277
 She even used her position to secretly keep his book for herself. 

118
00:10:15,527 --> 00:10:21,477
 It feels like my favorite dress in the display window is being coveted by someone else 

119
00:10:21,477 --> 00:10:22,887
 who has paid the deposit for it. 

120
00:10:22,887 --> 00:10:25,157
 She is already one step ahead. 

121
00:10:38,677 --> 00:10:41,517
   

122
00:10:41,517 --> 00:10:45,307
   
   
   

123
00:10:49,727 --> 00:10:51,547
   

124
00:10:51,547 --> 00:10:53,527
   

125
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:58,670
 Is she talking about me? 

126
00:11:16,417 --> 00:11:19,747
   

127
00:11:31,047 --> 00:11:34,277
What does this even mean?

128
00:11:39,437 --> 00:11:41,899
According to the class group, the Book Exchange Event will end soon.

129
00:11:41,899 --> 00:11:44,187
Remember to return the book.

130
00:11:45,677 --> 00:11:48,587
I'm still at the prologue.

131
00:11:53,887 --> 00:11:56,167
Help me return this book.

132
00:11:56,167 --> 00:11:59,267
I have a match in two days, and I think we'll have extra training every day.

133
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:01,987
You actually took a book from the exchange?

134
00:12:02,957 --> 00:12:04,167
It's none of your business.

135
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:07,587
I haven't asked you. What book are you reading?

136
00:12:08,287 --> 00:12:10,317
History of Medicine?

137
00:12:10,317 --> 00:12:12,837
It looks like a book from one of our classmates.

138
00:12:12,837 --> 00:12:14,647
This is my book.

139
00:12:14,647 --> 00:12:16,957
I didn't pick up any book from the Book Exchange Event.

140
00:12:16,957 --> 00:12:19,407
I didn't find anything I wanted to read.

141
00:12:19,407 --> 00:12:22,797
I couldn't find that Neuropsychology book either.

142
00:12:25,827 --> 00:12:28,067
What is this smell in the book? It's choking me.

143
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:30,220
It's perfume. You don't understand.

144
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:31,747
You don't understand the beauty of perfume.

145
00:12:31,747 --> 00:12:34,247
I thought you disliked perfume.

146
00:12:35,247 --> 00:12:36,837
Yes.

147
00:12:36,837 --> 00:12:42,477
I just don't like the type of perfume that’s too overwhelming.

148
00:12:42,477 --> 00:12:44,827
This one is different.

149
00:12:46,407 --> 00:12:48,197
This is the smell of knowledge.

150
00:12:48,197 --> 00:12:53,827
After smelling it, it can purify and resonate with my soul.

151
00:12:55,247 --> 00:12:56,957
I'll get going now.

152
00:12:56,957 --> 00:13:00,557
Write something meaningful on the front of my book.

153
00:13:00,557 --> 00:13:05,477
Make it look sincere and deep.

154
00:13:05,477 --> 00:13:07,367
Make sure your writing is nice too.

155
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:09,347
You can write it now.

156
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:12,347
Why so serious all of a sudden?

157
00:13:14,247 --> 00:13:16,007
What should I write?

158
00:13:16,007 --> 00:13:19,767
Let me see. Find a good quote.

159
00:13:19,767 --> 00:13:21,187
What about this?

160
00:13:21,187 --> 00:13:24,107
This one? I don't think it's good enough.

161
00:13:24,107 --> 00:13:26,207
Then let's choose another.

162
00:13:26,887 --> 00:13:29,597
This one. This one. What do you think?

163
00:13:29,597 --> 00:13:32,297
I think this will do.

164
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:37,560
Where can it be?

165
00:13:39,077 --> 00:13:41,597
I lost my nerve...

166
00:13:41,597 --> 00:13:44,007
Aren't your nerves in your mind?

167
00:13:44,007 --> 00:13:45,597
No.

168
00:13:45,597 --> 00:13:49,047
I'm talking about that amazing book of mine.

169
00:13:49,047 --> 00:13:51,557
Maybe they haven't returned it yet.

170
00:13:51,557 --> 00:13:53,747
Where is my nerve-book?

171
00:13:57,407 --> 00:14:00,527
Isn’t this Song Cong's book?

172
00:14:00,527 --> 00:14:04,437
I don't know who took it. I haven't read it.

173
00:14:04,437 --> 00:14:06,347
You can read it now.

174
00:14:08,677 --> 00:14:12,867
It's shameful to spy on someone else's privacy...

175
00:14:14,166 --> 00:14:15,197
   

176
00:14:15,197 --> 00:14:23,987
"Make sure you marry someone who laughs at the same things you do..."

177
00:14:34,127 --> 00:14:36,077
Qi Qi.

178
00:14:37,887 --> 00:14:39,627
Qi Qi.

179
00:14:41,957 --> 00:14:43,837
What's wrong?

180
00:14:43,837 --> 00:14:45,797
Nothing.

181
00:14:46,837 --> 00:14:48,597
Have you found your book?

182
00:14:48,597 --> 00:14:50,947
No.

183
00:14:51,677 --> 00:14:54,127
It must be because my book is too interesting.

184
00:14:54,127 --> 00:14:56,347
So that person doesn't want to return it.

185
00:14:59,717 --> 00:15:01,957
By the way, what book did you choose?

186
00:15:01,957 --> 00:15:04,557
Can I read it?

187
00:15:04,557 --> 00:15:06,757
Go ahead.

188
00:15:06,757 --> 00:15:09,767
   

189
00:15:09,767 --> 00:15:14,197
"Thank you for showing me how to be true to myself.

190
00:15:14,197 --> 00:15:19,527
I hope I can be a star in the light of your life."

191
00:15:19,527 --> 00:15:21,317
This comment is good.

192
00:15:21,317 --> 00:15:23,917
And the handwriting is...

193
00:15:26,077 --> 00:15:28,837
Isn't this Song Cong's handwriting?

194
00:15:28,837 --> 00:15:30,197
Really?

195
00:15:30,197 --> 00:15:34,027
Yes. It looks exactly like the handwriting in Song Cong's notes.

196
00:15:34,027 --> 00:15:35,917
Show me.

197
00:15:47,957 --> 00:15:54,490
 That time, I didn't understand why Qi Qi 

198
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:58,820
 would be so happy over a short paragraph. 

199
00:16:23,717 --> 00:16:27,717
Well... After my training later, I'll go to Cong's house to study.

200
00:16:27,717 --> 00:16:29,957
Bye, Huan Er.

201
00:16:29,957 --> 00:16:31,797
Qi Qi.

202
00:16:32,407 --> 00:16:34,560
Are you reading?

203
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:36,120
Bye.

204
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,717
Huan Er, are you going to study later?

205
00:16:40,717 --> 00:16:42,517
Can I join?

206
00:16:43,527 --> 00:16:46,557
The tuition class my mom signed me up for isn't good.

207
00:16:46,557 --> 00:16:49,000
Sure. This is great!

208
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,517
- Let's go. 
 - Let's go.

209
00:17:07,677 --> 00:17:09,127
Song Cong.

210
00:17:09,127 --> 00:17:13,327
Can you lend me The Catcher in the Rye that you offered at the Book Exchange Event?

211
00:17:13,327 --> 00:17:15,147
Sure.

212
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:20,327
I love this book too.

213
00:17:20,327 --> 00:17:24,907
I think you can resonate well with the protagonist, right?

214
00:17:29,847 --> 00:17:32,187
I'm coming.

215
00:17:35,957 --> 00:17:37,437
You're here quite early today.

216
00:17:37,437 --> 00:17:39,557
Where were you?

217
00:17:40,277 --> 00:17:42,757
I went to buy a handbook.

218
00:17:42,757 --> 00:17:45,517
You bought a handbook?

219
00:17:45,517 --> 00:17:47,237
Mind your own business.

220
00:17:47,237 --> 00:17:48,367
What did you buy? Show me.

221
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:49,407
- Wait. 
 - Show me.

222
00:17:49,407 --> 00:17:52,277
Wait. I bought it to improve my grade.

223
00:17:52,277 --> 00:17:54,040
I can't show it to you. You can buy it yourself.

224
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,887
You're so petty. Fine. I won't read it.

225
00:17:56,887 --> 00:17:59,627
- It's not that precious. 
 - Then don't look.

226
00:18:13,717 --> 00:18:16,167
Qi Qi, you must be tired after all that studying.

227
00:18:16,167 --> 00:18:17,600
I bought these chicken wings for you.

228
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:21,197
Eat some and keep studying hard after.

229
00:18:21,197 --> 00:18:22,640
Thank you.

230
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:26,864
But I don't think I need them this time.

231
00:18:26,864 --> 00:18:28,037
I got a pretty good grade this time.

232
00:18:28,037 --> 00:18:31,327
It means those chicken wings actually worked.

233
00:18:31,327 --> 00:18:34,647
If I can improve after eating these wings, I want to try them too.

234
00:18:34,647 --> 00:18:36,167
Wait. What are you doing?

235
00:18:36,167 --> 00:18:38,607
They may work for Qi Qi, but they may not work for you.

236
00:18:38,607 --> 00:18:41,887
Qi Qi, can you give me one?

237
00:18:41,887 --> 00:18:43,647
Let's share them.

238
00:18:43,647 --> 00:18:45,520
See? Qi Qi agreed to give me one.

239
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,480
- Eat it. 
 - Eat.

240
00:18:49,327 --> 00:18:50,847
Qi Qi.

241
00:18:50,847 --> 00:18:54,237
How many people did you surpass this time?

242
00:18:54,237 --> 00:18:55,717
Didn't you check?

243
00:18:55,717 --> 00:18:57,647
Around ten people.

244
00:18:57,647 --> 00:18:59,807
That's good.

245
00:18:59,807 --> 00:19:01,557
That's good.

246
00:19:02,647 --> 00:19:04,347
What about you?

247
00:19:08,517 --> 00:19:11,717
I failed again this time.

248
00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:13,477
I got last place.

249
00:19:14,197 --> 00:19:15,437
Pray for yourself.

250
00:19:15,437 --> 00:19:17,967
There'll be a parent-teacher conference this time.

251
00:19:18,957 --> 00:19:21,127
A parent-teacher conference?

252
00:19:21,127 --> 00:19:22,477
Says who?

253
00:19:22,477 --> 00:19:24,807
Mr. Xu.

254
00:19:24,807 --> 00:19:27,957
You all know about that?

255
00:19:31,167 --> 00:19:32,807
I'm doomed.

256
00:19:32,807 --> 00:19:35,037
Here goes my new phone.

257
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,275
This is delicious.

258
00:19:40,275 --> 00:19:42,167
Of course.

259
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:43,997
It costs five yuan.

260
00:19:53,517 --> 00:19:55,237
Eat more.

261
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:01,480
Mom.

262
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:05,023
You won't attend the parent-teacher conference, right?

263
00:20:05,023 --> 00:20:06,677
I have a business trip tomorrow.

264
00:20:06,677 --> 00:20:09,517
I'll inform your homeroom teacher about it.

