00:21:00,927 --> 00:21:01,997
My fellow parents,

268
00:21:01,997 --> 00:21:05,037
have you read the transcript? 
    

269
00:21:05,037 --> 00:21:08,327
We can objectively check your children's

270
00:21:08,327 --> 00:21:10,407
current learning progress. 
    

271
00:21:10,407 --> 00:21:14,127
Song Cong in our class always has good grades.

272
00:21:14,127 --> 00:21:15,607
His performance is consistent.

273
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:20,037
There are also some students like our new transfer,

274
00:21:20,037 --> 00:21:21,167
Chen Huan Er.

275
00:21:21,167 --> 00:21:23,887
Although her foundation isn't as good,

276
00:21:23,887 --> 00:21:27,647
she has been catching up and improved tremendously.

277
00:21:27,647 --> 00:21:32,407
However, there are a few students in our class who aren't doing well.

278
00:21:32,407 --> 00:21:36,867
Their grades fluctuate like our blood pressure.

279
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:40,717
Their grades show exactly how much they must be slacking off.

280
00:21:40,717 --> 00:21:44,517
Don't think that sending your children to school will solve everything.

281
00:21:44,517 --> 00:21:48,200
Don't just count on the teachers to educate them.

282
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:52,113
You have to supervise them at home too.

283
00:21:52,113 --> 00:21:54,237
Jing Xi Chi's mom.

284
00:21:55,167 --> 00:21:57,107
What do you think?

285
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:06,747
Mr. Xu.

286
00:22:06,747 --> 00:22:10,567
I think it's quite normal that their examination results

287
00:22:10,567 --> 00:22:12,080
fluctuate from time to time.

288
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:16,237
Although Li Tian doesn't have that issue.

289
00:22:16,237 --> 00:22:18,037
He did quite well this time.

290
00:22:18,037 --> 00:22:21,647
How about I share with everyone how we did it?

291
00:22:21,647 --> 00:22:24,077
Okay. Please go ahead.

292
00:22:29,607 --> 00:22:34,087
Actually, when it comes to educating our children,

293
00:22:34,087 --> 00:22:36,717
we have to be supportive and encouraging.

294
00:22:36,717 --> 00:22:39,347
It's very important to pay attention to their mental well-being.

295
00:22:39,347 --> 00:22:42,237
We cannot break their confidence.

296
00:22:42,237 --> 00:22:45,167
Li Tian has always been proactive in his studies.

297
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:47,167
I'm really thankful to you today.

298
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:50,407
Just now, my mind went blank.

299
00:22:50,407 --> 00:22:51,957
I would be the same if I were you.

300
00:22:51,957 --> 00:22:53,807
I can't believe their homeroom teacher.

301
00:22:53,807 --> 00:22:55,327
How can he be so callous?

302
00:22:55,327 --> 00:22:57,887
Moreover, this kind of ranking is problematic too.

303
00:22:57,887 --> 00:23:01,087
In my opinion, they should do this in private.

304
00:23:01,087 --> 00:23:05,237
Exposing everyone's results like this is like a public trial.

305
00:23:05,237 --> 00:23:07,517
Actually, the teachers are doing it for the students.

306
00:23:07,517 --> 00:23:09,347
There's a reason for this ranking.

307
00:23:09,347 --> 00:23:12,327
I can only blame my son for being too bad at his studies.

308
00:23:12,327 --> 00:23:14,237
I'll teach him a lesson when I get back.

309
00:23:14,237 --> 00:23:16,997
I feel so embarrassed today.

310
00:23:16,997 --> 00:23:18,717
You can't be like this.

311
00:23:18,717 --> 00:23:20,887
No matter what, he is your son.

312
00:23:20,887 --> 00:23:24,367
Your child will never look down on you, so you shouldn't look down on him either.

313
00:23:24,367 --> 00:23:29,517
Li Tian only got second place this time. But what can I say?

314
00:23:29,517 --> 00:23:32,907
Is second place not good enough?

315
00:23:35,317 --> 00:23:36,957
Oh, yes.

316
00:23:36,957 --> 00:23:40,087
A family of doctors should aim for first.

317
00:23:40,087 --> 00:23:42,367
So, it's expected of him.

318
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:44,087
Yes.

319
00:23:44,087 --> 00:23:47,927
Getting second place is like failing the imperial examination.

320
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:54,277
Dr. Li wants me to organize a family meeting to come up with a solution.

321
00:23:54,277 --> 00:23:59,807
If it wasn't for Dr. Li's reputation, I wouldn't make him study so hard.

322
00:23:59,807 --> 00:24:03,567
Yes, it's not easy for you either.

323
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:05,477
Let's go.

324
00:24:14,437 --> 00:24:16,587
I'll get going now. Bye.

325
00:24:17,327 --> 00:24:19,567
What are you doing?

326
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:22,517
You bought me milk tea and strolled around with me.

327
00:24:22,517 --> 00:24:23,957
Huan Er.

328
00:24:23,957 --> 00:24:26,437
I treat you fairly.

329
00:24:26,437 --> 00:24:28,517
Right?

330
00:24:29,237 --> 00:24:30,657
Are you sure?

331
00:24:30,657 --> 00:24:33,477
I bought chicken wings for you yesterday, right?

332
00:24:33,477 --> 00:24:35,127
Did you buy them for me?

333
00:24:35,127 --> 00:24:38,037
- Did you eat them or not? 
 - I just ate a wingtip.

334
00:24:38,037 --> 00:24:39,197
What about the milk tea?

335
00:24:39,197 --> 00:24:41,197
I treated you twice.

336
00:24:41,197 --> 00:24:44,907
Shouldn't you do me a favor?

337
00:24:47,607 --> 00:24:49,647
What do you need?

338
00:24:49,647 --> 00:24:51,607
You don't have to do anything.

339
00:24:51,607 --> 00:24:54,927
You just have to come with me and leave everything to me.

340
00:24:54,927 --> 00:24:58,427
Anyway, my life is in your hands now.

341
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,437
No.

342
00:25:01,437 --> 00:25:04,997
- Chen Huan Er, just give me a hand. 
 - I want to go home.

343
00:25:04,997 --> 00:25:06,757
Your home is just nearby.

344
00:25:06,757 --> 00:25:07,847
Let's go.

345
00:25:07,847 --> 00:25:10,087
Huan Er, help me. I really need your help.

346
00:25:10,087 --> 00:25:11,167
What are you doing?

347
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:13,197
I swear I'll take you home right after this.

348
00:25:13,197 --> 00:25:14,387
- Mom. 
 - Don't worry.

349
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:15,927
Mom.

350
00:25:15,927 --> 00:25:17,867
Let's go.

351
00:25:17,867 --> 00:25:20,427
   

352
00:25:30,517 --> 00:25:31,887
Jing Xi Chi.

353
00:25:31,887 --> 00:25:34,880
How dare you come back?

354
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,710
You...

355
00:25:40,847 --> 00:25:42,167
You are here too, Huan Er.

356
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:43,997
Aunt Lin.

357
00:25:47,647 --> 00:25:49,567
I don't understand.

358
00:25:49,567 --> 00:25:52,167
How did you score so badly?

359
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:53,807
Studying is easy.

360
00:25:53,807 --> 00:25:54,957
You just have to study.

361
00:25:54,957 --> 00:25:57,407
How did you get this result? Tell me.

362
00:25:57,407 --> 00:25:58,757
I'm sorry, Mom.

363
00:25:58,757 --> 00:26:00,087
I'm an unfilial child.

364
00:26:00,087 --> 00:26:01,847
I've embarrassed you.

365
00:26:01,847 --> 00:26:05,367
But look, I brought Huan Er over to help me study.

366
00:26:05,367 --> 00:26:07,477
I want to study hard too.

367
00:26:07,477 --> 00:26:09,037
We'll get back to studying now.

368
00:26:09,037 --> 00:26:10,287
We have to study now.

369
00:26:10,287 --> 00:26:12,047
- I... 
 - Let's go and start studying.

370
00:26:12,047 --> 00:26:14,667
- What are we studying? 
 - We'll study now.

371
00:26:22,277 --> 00:26:24,107
Have a seat.

372
00:26:32,757 --> 00:26:35,437
Why did you bring me to your house?

373
00:26:35,437 --> 00:26:36,677
Isn't it obvious?

374
00:26:36,677 --> 00:26:38,037
To help me with my studies.

375
00:26:38,037 --> 00:26:39,647
I didn't do well on the exam this time.

376
00:26:39,647 --> 00:26:42,757
But I need to placate my mom.

377
00:26:42,757 --> 00:26:46,037
If I ask Cong, he'll be very serious about it.

378
00:26:46,037 --> 00:26:48,407
But I don't expect you to teach me anything.

379
00:26:48,407 --> 00:26:50,717
You can just do your homework here.

380
00:26:50,717 --> 00:26:52,407
Are you looking down on me?

381
00:26:52,407 --> 00:26:55,907
I'm more than capable of tutoring you.

382
00:27:09,647 --> 00:27:12,317
What is this?

383
00:27:12,997 --> 00:27:16,127
You left this political history question blank.

384
00:27:16,127 --> 00:27:18,567
I take it you were too lazy to memorize it.

385
00:27:18,567 --> 00:27:22,740
But what about the physical chemistry questions?

386
00:27:22,740 --> 00:27:24,277
They asked the same thing.

387
00:27:24,277 --> 00:27:28,120
You got the multiple-choice questions right, but you failed the longer problem-solving ones.

388
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:31,101
You expect me to believe you're that dumb?

389
00:27:31,101 --> 00:27:33,237
I am that dumb.

390
00:27:36,517 --> 00:27:38,037
Why did you get bad grades on purpose?

391
00:27:38,037 --> 00:27:40,080
Chen Huan Er, tutor me if you can.

392
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:43,080
If not, don't blame me.

393
00:27:44,237 --> 00:27:45,757
Aunt Lin.

394
00:27:45,757 --> 00:27:49,007
- Aunt Lin. 
 - Chen Huan Er.

395
00:27:49,007 --> 00:27:50,087
Hurry up and come back.

396
00:27:50,087 --> 00:27:52,477
What are you doing? Why are you so nervous?

397
00:27:52,477 --> 00:27:54,717
Why are you so nervous?

398
00:27:56,567 --> 00:27:58,327
Actually, it was like this.

399
00:27:58,327 --> 00:28:01,957
I just randomly picked the answers for the multiple-choice questions.

400
00:28:01,957 --> 00:28:05,520
I was just lucky to get them right.

401
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,220
Are you not going to tell me the truth?

402
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:10,237
- Aunt Lin. 
 - Chen Huan Er.

403
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:21,717
I don't want to get better grades than Qi Qi.

404
00:28:21,717 --> 00:28:23,567
Don't tell Qi Qi about it.

405
00:28:23,567 --> 00:28:27,127
Don't tell anyone.

406
00:28:27,127 --> 00:28:28,920
Promise me.

407
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:30,550
Okay.

408
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:32,693
That's more like it.

409
00:28:32,693 --> 00:28:34,513
Do your homework.

410
00:28:43,167 --> 00:28:47,880
 Although Jing Xi Chi told me his secret, 

411
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:52,840
 I don't know why my heart feels heavy. 

412
00:28:52,847 --> 00:28:57,757
 It seems like everyone's relationships have become complicated. 

413
00:28:58,367 --> 00:29:04,327
 Sometimes, ignorance is bliss. 

414
00:29:19,277 --> 00:29:22,277
Neuropsychology.

415
00:29:22,277 --> 00:29:23,367
Huan Er.

416
00:29:23,367 --> 00:29:25,387
Are you looking for a book?

417
00:29:26,197 --> 00:29:28,807
I still can't find the book I offered at the Book Exchange Event.

418
00:29:28,807 --> 00:29:31,887
By the way, my book is called Neuropsychology. Have you seen it?

419
00:29:31,887 --> 00:29:34,327
I looked around to see what everyone took.

420
00:29:34,327 --> 00:29:36,437
But I didn't see yours.

421
00:29:36,437 --> 00:29:39,517
Did someone from another class take it?

422
00:29:39,517 --> 00:29:41,757
Really?

423
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:50,367
The Catcher in the Rye. 
    

424
00:29:50,367 --> 00:29:52,167
You put this book in the exchange too?

425
00:29:52,167 --> 00:29:53,277
Yes.

426
00:29:53,277 --> 00:29:56,087
I saw someone offer the same book.

427
00:29:56,087 --> 00:29:57,887
So I chose that person's book too.

428
00:29:57,887 --> 00:30:02,237
I wonder if he chose mine as well.

429
00:30:02,237 --> 00:30:03,677
But you already have this book.

430
00:30:03,677 --> 00:30:05,847
Why did you choose the same book?

431
00:30:05,847 --> 00:30:07,957
The content isn't important.

432
00:30:07,957 --> 00:30:13,927
What matters is choosing the same book, or having someone choose your book.

433
00:30:13,927 --> 00:30:15,757
How do I explain it?

434
00:30:15,757 --> 00:30:17,437
Although talking about fate is tacky,

435
00:30:17,437 --> 00:30:21,907
don't you think it's precious when the probability is so low?

436
00:30:25,167 --> 00:30:29,717
 I only vaguely understood what Xin Yan said. 

437
00:30:30,517 --> 00:30:35,607
 I only understand those words after many years. 

438
00:30:35,607 --> 00:30:36,527
   

439
00:30:36,527 --> 00:30:41,220
 Two sentences on the same page, appearing together in a single moment... 

440
00:30:41,220 --> 00:30:44,750
 That might be the closest two people will ever be. 

441
00:31:09,627 --> 00:31:15,050
   

442
00:31:25,517 --> 00:31:30,587
   

443
00:31:36,107 --> 00:31:37,767
   

444
00:31:37,767 --> 00:31:39,797
   

445
00:31:39,797 --> 00:31:43,107
   

446
00:31:58,987 --> 00:32:00,647
   

447
00:32:00,647 --> 00:32:03,827
   

448
00:32:11,567 --> 00:32:13,997
Jing Xi Chi.

449
00:32:13,997 --> 00:32:16,717
Which book did you offer at the Book Exchange Event?

450
00:32:16,717 --> 00:32:18,567
I didn't offer any books.

451
00:32:18,567 --> 00:32:21,717
With how little I have, what book can I offer?

452
00:32:22,847 --> 00:32:24,607
Then why did you go to the library?

453
00:32:24,607 --> 00:32:26,797
I was just helping Cong out.

454
00:32:30,277 --> 00:32:31,437
 Qi Qi. 

455
00:32:31,437 --> 00:32:32,677
 What book did you offer? 

456
00:32:32,677 --> 00:32:34,127
 It's called The Fountainhead. 

457
00:32:34,127 --> 00:32:37,107
 It's my favorite novel. 

458
00:32:39,287 --> 00:32:41,717
 Wait. I bought it to improve my grade. 

459
00:32:41,717 --> 00:32:43,520
 I can't show it to you. You can buy it yourself. 

460
00:32:43,520 --> 00:32:47,520
 You're so petty. Fine. I won't read it. 

461
00:32:57,327 --> 00:32:58,960
 Xin Yan, come forward. 

462
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:01,887
Distribute these science or art stream application forms to your classmates.

463
00:33:01,887 --> 00:33:03,407
- Okay. 
 - Students.

464
00:33:03,407 --> 00:33:06,087
After you get your science or art stream application form,

465
00:33:06,087 --> 00:33:09,567
go back and discuss it with your parents.

466
00:33:09,567 --> 00:33:13,607
It will affect your college major selection

467
00:33:13,607 --> 00:33:16,237
and your future career.

468
00:33:16,237 --> 00:33:20,800
If there's anything you don't understand, you can come to me.

469
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:22,440
Class dismissed.

470
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:29,560
Song Cong, you and Xi Chi will choose the science stream, right?

471
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:31,760
We will both choose the science stream.

472
00:33:37,647 --> 00:33:39,367
Huan Er.

473
00:33:39,367 --> 00:33:42,600
What stream do you want to choose?

474
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:44,401
It's obvious I'll do better in the science stream.

475
00:33:44,401 --> 00:33:46,440
So I'll choose science.

476
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,826
I'll choose science too.

477
00:33:47,826 --> 00:33:50,237
My grades in science subjects this time aren't bad.

478
00:33:50,237 --> 00:33:52,717
That way, we won't be separated.

479
00:33:52,717 --> 00:33:56,160
Don't you have to discuss it with your mom?

480
00:33:56,160 --> 00:34:00,037
It's fine. I can imitate my mom's signature very well.

481
00:34:00,037 --> 00:34:01,477
Are you sure?

482
00:34:01,477 --> 00:34:03,997
Imitating her signature is not the safest option.

483
00:34:03,997 --> 00:34:06,997
The safest option is to sign it yourself from the start.

484
00:34:06,997 --> 00:34:08,687
That's enough.

485
00:34:08,687 --> 00:34:11,557
How dare you discuss such blasphemy right in front of us?

486
00:34:11,557 --> 00:34:14,787
Don't influence my kind and pure Huan Er.

487
00:34:22,637 --> 00:34:25,587
Mr. Xu.

488
00:34:27,267 --> 00:34:30,957
   

489
00:34:30,957 --> 00:34:32,077
   

490
00:34:32,077 --> 00:34:33,467
   

491
00:34:33,467 --> 00:34:35,087
   

492
00:34:41,717 --> 00:34:46,080
   

493
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:50,303
I hope I can also be a star in the light of your life.

494
00:34:50,303 --> 00:34:52,170
   

495
00:34:59,327 --> 00:35:02,437
I asked the nanny to cook pig heart soup especially for you.

496
00:35:02,437 --> 00:35:03,957
Why haven't you drunk it?

497
00:35:03,957 --> 00:35:05,917
It's good for your mind.

498
00:35:06,847 --> 00:35:09,227
I was studying just now.

499
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:13,767
I know your class will soon split into art and science streams.

500
00:35:13,767 --> 00:35:15,997
I've already signed it with your homeroom teacher.

501
00:35:15,997 --> 00:35:17,957
You'll go into the art stream.

502
00:35:24,927 --> 00:35:26,837
Mom.

503
00:35:28,367 --> 00:35:30,557
There are more science majors at universities.

504
00:35:30,557 --> 00:35:33,727
I can go to a better university if I enter science.

505
00:35:33,727 --> 00:35:36,437
That doesn't make sense.

506
00:35:36,437 --> 00:35:40,640
If you can't do well, you can't get into a good university, no matter the stream.

507
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,727
Objectively, science isn't for you.

508
00:35:42,727 --> 00:35:46,707
Besides, you like writing and want to be an author, right?

509
00:35:47,597 --> 00:35:51,847
Are you asking me to take art so you can be an author?

510
00:35:51,847 --> 00:35:55,227
You just want me to be a lawyer like you.

511
00:35:57,557 --> 00:36:01,347
All your friends chose science, right?

512
00:36:02,597 --> 00:36:03,997
Let me tell you.

513
00:36:03,997 --> 00:36:06,207
This isn't about loyalty.

514
00:36:06,207 --> 00:36:09,287
You're not taking your future seriously.

515
00:36:09,287 --> 00:36:11,517
Friends are just passing figures in life.

516
00:36:11,517 --> 00:36:14,157
They won't be responsible for your future.

517
00:36:14,157 --> 00:36:17,360
Changing your life for them is just wishful thinking.

518
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:19,653
I can be responsible for my own wishful thinking.

519
00:36:19,653 --> 00:36:21,887
How are you going to do that?

520
00:36:21,887 --> 00:36:24,117
- I... 
 - You are my daughter.

521
00:36:24,117 --> 00:36:26,957
That's why I'm saying this.

522
00:36:26,957 --> 00:36:29,427
Back then, you said private schools weren't good.

523
00:36:29,427 --> 00:36:30,767
So I sent you to a public school.

524
00:36:30,767 --> 00:36:33,229
You said the experimental high school was bad, so I sent you to Tianhe.

525
00:36:33,229 --> 00:36:34,880
I will not tolerate you anymore.

526
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:37,674
If you throw a tantrum over class selection,

527
00:36:37,674 --> 00:36:39,637
I'll send you abroad immediately.

528
00:36:39,637 --> 00:36:41,920
You can go abroad, attend their high school,

529
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:44,487
and then you won't have to choose a stream.

530
00:36:47,767 --> 00:36:49,707
Fine.

531
00:36:55,800 --> 00:37:02,287
Can I invite my classmates over for my birthday?

532
00:37:02,287 --> 00:37:03,847
Just for a meal.

533
00:37:03,847 --> 00:37:06,517
It won't affect my studies.

534
00:37:06,517 --> 00:37:08,847
